---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Belvedere Decks | Composite Deck Builder in Montgomery County, MD"
  description="Montgomery County's straight-answer deck company. Premium TimberTech and Trex composite decks with published pricing, an exact price at your kitchen table the same visit, and a 10-year workmanship warranty."
>
  <!-- HERO — full-height charcoal, matching the BOL homepage structure -->
  <section class="hero" style="min-height: calc(100vh - 64px); display: flex; flex-direction: column; padding: 0;">
    <div class="container" style="flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; padding-top: 64px; padding-bottom: 64px;">
      <p class="eyebrow">Montgomery County, Maryland</p>
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 12px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">
        Belvedere Decks
      </h2>
      <h1 style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.75rem); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
        Your exact deck price,<br />same visit.
      </h1>
      <p class="lead" style="margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
        Most deck companies make you wait a week for a number. We measure your deck,
        build your estimate on the iPad in front of you, and hand you an exact price
        before we leave — with three options and nothing hidden.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a class="btn primary" href="/contact" style="padding: 16px 32px;">Book Your Consultation</a>
        <a class="btn ghost" href="/pricing" style="padding: 16px 32px;">See What Decks Really Cost</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-bar">
      <div class="container">
        <p>TimberTech &amp; Trex Installer · 10-Year Workmanship Warranty · MCDPS Permit Fluency · Serving Montgomery County</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROOF BAR -->
  <section class="proof-bar">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cells">
        <div>
          <p class="big">Published Pricing</p>
          <p class="label">The county's only real numbers</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="big">Same-Visit Price</p>
          <p class="label">Exact, on the iPad, in your kitchen</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="big">10-Year Warranty</p>
          <p class="label">Workmanship, in writing</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Three ways to get a new deck</p>
      <h2>Only pay for what your deck actually needs.</h2>
      <p class="lead">
        Most Montgomery County decks built between 1985 and 2010 have framing with decades
        of life left — under boards and railings that are done. We inspect honestly and
        match the project to the deck, not to our invoice.
      </p>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 36px;">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Deck Refloor</h3>
          <p class="price">$14,000–$20,000</p>
          <p>Your frame stays. We replace the walking surface with premium composite boards and hidden fasteners — typical 300–400 sq ft projects.</p>
          <a href="/services/deck-refloor">Refloor details →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Deck Facelift</h3>
          <p class="price">$24,000–$35,000</p>
          <p>New boards, new railings, new fascia on your existing frame. The biggest transformation per dollar in deck building — around 400 sq ft.</p>
          <a href="/services/deck-facelift">Facelift details →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Custom Deck</h3>
          <p class="price">$40,000–$75,000+</p>
          <p>Fully custom, engineered, permitted, and inspected. A two-visit design process that ends with drawings and a fixed price — not a guess.</p>
          <a href="/services/custom-decks">Custom details →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Why homeowners choose us</p>
      <h2>The parts of a deck you can't see at the barbecue.</h2>
      <div class="grid cols-2" style="margin-top: 24px;">
        <div>
          <h3>Prices in writing, before we visit</h3>
          <p>We're the only deck company in Montgomery County publishing real project pricing. Read <a href="/pricing">what decks really cost</a> before anyone sits in your kitchen.</p>
          <h3>Code-first construction</h3>
          <p>Footings to 30″ below grade. Full ledger flashing. Structural connectors with every fastener hole filled. Joists at composite-correct spacing. These are the items cheap bids quietly omit — and exactly what we walk you through on your own deck.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>10-year workmanship warranty</h3>
          <p>In writing, on every project — on top of the 25–50-year manufacturer warranties on TimberTech and Trex boards.</p>
          <h3>County permit fluency</h3>
          <p>MCDPS permits, footing/framing/final inspections, and HOA architectural review are our home turf — not a surcharge and not your problem. <a href="/montgomery-county-deck-permits">Read the permit guide</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2>From first call to finished deck.</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>1. Call or book</th><td>Tell us about the deck — by phone, or pick an appointment time right on the <a href="/contact">calendar</a>. Either way you'll get an honest price range up front.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>2. The visit</th><td>We walk the deck together and narrate what we find, good and bad: post condition, ledger flashing, joist spacing, railing safety. Then we measure and build your actual price on the iPad while you watch.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>3. Three options</th><td>Good, better, and best — same code-perfect structure under every tier. We never tier the safety.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>4. The build</th><td>Permits and inspections handled where required, a clean site every night, and a final walkthrough on your finished deck.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px;"><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Book your consultation</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where we work</p>
      <h2>Serving Montgomery County's neighborhoods.</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/towns/potomac">Potomac</a> ·
        <a href="/towns/north-potomac-kentlands">North Potomac &amp; Kentlands</a> ·
        <a href="/towns/bethesda">Bethesda</a> ·
        <a href="/towns/olney">Olney</a> ·
        <a href="/towns/boyds">Boyds</a> ·
        <a href="/towns/clarksburg">Clarksburg</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
